_json.description: Most evolutionists believe that the "tailbone" or more properly, "coccyx", is vestigial (a degenerate or imperfectly developed organ or structure that has little or no utility).  They think it proves that we humans once had a tail like a monkey since we supposedly evolved from them.  The coccyx is not a "useless leftover" from our primate ancestors but rather is very important in that it anchors muscles that contribute to sitting, standing and bowel control.
